<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="919" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15230.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State ad
                                    interim</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to
                                    Mexico</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>784. Your 631, June 12, 5 p.m. Silliman telegraphs that Foreign Office
                            requests him to express thanks of Carranza to Department and to you for
                            good offices in transmitting message of Cházaro and to say there is no
                            reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>